<span id="freeTextContainer17956260610636818395">Wow! This was <b>gripping</b>!<br/><br/><b>I had no idea it would be such a suspenseful read. I had so much fun binge-reading it!</b> I was drawn in from the first page. I kept trying to figure out how everything and everyone would be connected. The plot was more complex than I was expecting! It was the perfect mix of mystery and supernatural and the eerie winter atmosphere was perfectly described.<br/><br/>I absolutely loved <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/54303987.The_Drowning_Kind' title='The Drowning Kind by Jennifer McMahon' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Drowning Kind</a>, so I knew I had to read The Winter People sooner than later. I got a copy from the li</span>
  <span id="freeText17956260610636818395" style="display:none">Wow! This was <b>gripping</b>!<br /><br /><b>I had no idea it would be such a suspenseful read. I had so much fun binge-reading it!</b> I was drawn in from the first page. I kept trying to figure out how everything and everyone would be connected. The plot was more complex than I was expecting! It was the perfect mix of mystery and supernatural and the eerie winter atmosphere was perfectly described.<br /><br />I absolutely loved <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/54303987.The_Drowning_Kind" title="The Drowning Kind by Jennifer McMahon" rel="nofollow noopener">The Drowning Kind</a>, so I knew I had to read The Winter People sooner than later. I got a copy from the library in February... and only read it three months later! I always wait for the right time to read each book of my TBR. How do I know what time is right? Reader instinct! I was in a reading slump when I finally picked this one and, thanks to Mcmahon, I'm now back on track!<br /><br />Little anecdote: it was impossible for me to picture Lucius with another face than Lucius Malefoy's haha!!<br /><br /><i>4.5 rounded up</i></span>
