                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer2682959250&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2682959250" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17508316187711277000">The Winter People is a tale about how love can be mangled and twisted into horror. The loss of their beautiful , little girl, Gertie shatters a young couple who have little else to live for. As the mother Sara becomes unhinged with grief, she tries something desperate taught her by her witchlike Auntie, a spell to raise the dead. Men don&apos;t seem to to be nearly as strong or cunning as the women in the story and are sort of peripheral characters. Two major twists left me gobsmacked towards the end</span>
  <span id="freeText17508316187711277000" style="display:none">The Winter People is a tale about how love can be mangled and twisted into horror. The loss of their beautiful , little girl, Gertie shatters a young couple who have little else to live for. As the mother Sara becomes unhinged with grief, she tries something desperate taught her by her witchlike Auntie, a spell to raise the dead. Men don't seem to to be nearly as strong or cunning as the women in the story and are sort of peripheral characters. Two major twists left me gobsmacked towards the end.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17508316187711277000" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


