<div id="review_1784980112" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1784980112" />
    <a title="Lindsay - Traveling Sisters Book Reviews" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54886546-lindsay---traveling-sisters-book-reviews"><img alt="Lindsay - Traveling Sisters Book Reviews" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1472552597p2/54886546.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1784980112?book_show_action=true">Jun 04, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lindsay - Traveling Sisters Book Reviews" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lindsay - Traveling Sisters Book Reviews" href="/user/show/54886546-lindsay---traveling-sisters-book-reviews">Lindsay - Traveling Sisters Book Reviews</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54886546-lindsay---traveling-sisters-book-reviews?shelf=traveling-sister-read">traveling-sister-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1784980112" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10725837959887866321">3.5 stars. <br/><br/>Atmospheric. Suspenseful. Eerie.<br/><br/>After reading and loving this authors latest release, The Drowning Kind, I immediately wanted to get my hands on her backlist. This was a unique and engrossing story with a large supernatural aspect.<br/><br/>Supernatural is a hit or miss for me. This author has such a magical way with words, that her supernatural elements totally work for me. I can clearly envision her characters, atmosphere and storyline even with the ghost-y aspects.<br/><br/>This book was told through </span>
  <span id="freeText10725837959887866321" style="display:none">3.5 stars. <br /><br />Atmospheric. Suspenseful. Eerie.<br /><br />After reading and loving this authors latest release, The Drowning Kind, I immediately wanted to get my hands on her backlist. This was a unique and engrossing story with a large supernatural aspect.<br /><br />Supernatural is a hit or miss for me. This author has such a magical way with words, that her supernatural elements totally work for me. I can clearly envision her characters, atmosphere and storyline even with the ghost-y aspects.<br /><br />This book was told through a Past and Present timeline which included old diary entries. I loved this format but did find that the Past timeline was more intriguing and tension-filled. At times, I found myself confused between what happened during each time period, but I was able to sort the details out. A few of the elements in the second half of the Present timeline didn’t quite work for me, but I was able to roll with it. <br /><br />I truly enjoyed being wrapped up in this highly atmospheric ghost-y story. I look forward to reading more of her backlist! Thank you to my lovely local library for the loan of this book!</span>
  <a data-text-id="10725837959887866321" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


