<div id="review_851445551" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/851445551" />
    <a title="Rachel (TheShadesofOrange)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7487619-rachel-theshadesoforange"><img alt="Rachel (TheShadesofOrange)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1519620140p2/7487619.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/851445551?book_show_action=true">Feb 10, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rachel (TheShadesofOrange)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rachel (TheShadesofOrange)" href="/user/show/7487619-rachel-theshadesoforange">Rachel (TheShadesofOrange)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780385681452" href="/book/show/18007539-the-winter-people">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7487619-rachel-theshadesoforange?shelf=audiobooks">audiobooks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7487619-rachel-theshadesoforange?shelf=horror">horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer851445551" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11252721546062432476"><b>4.5 Stars - Delightfully Creepy</b><br/>This story is a perfect read for a cold, stormy winter night. While milder than more serious horror, McMahon weaves together a subtly disturbing story. The atmosphere was so well done. <br/><br/>This story itself is told over two different timelines: the early 1900s and the present. Personally, I preferred the reading the storyline in the past, finding it so much more intriguing than the modern mystery. If the entire story was had taken place in the past, I likely would have</span>
  <span id="freeText11252721546062432476" style="display:none"><b>4.5 Stars - Delightfully Creepy</b><br />This story is a perfect read for a cold, stormy winter night. While milder than more serious horror, McMahon weaves together a subtly disturbing story. The atmosphere was so well done. <br /><br />This story itself is told over two different timelines: the early 1900s and the present. Personally, I preferred the reading the storyline in the past, finding it so much more intriguing than the modern mystery. If the entire story was had taken place in the past, I likely would have rated the novel five stars. I really enjoyed those chapters! <br /><br />I would recommend this one to anyone who enjoys a quietly creepy story that will keep you turning pages to see what happens next... way too late into the night.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11252721546062432476" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


