<div id="review_839722110" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/839722110" />
    <a title="Sadie Hartmann" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28225370-sadie-hartmann"><img alt="Sadie Hartmann" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607526135p2/28225370.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/839722110?book_show_action=true">Jan 30, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sadie Hartmann" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sadie Hartmann" href="/user/show/28225370-sadie-hartmann">Sadie Hartmann</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer839722110" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18444472775273908853">The Winter People is one of the scariest books I have read in a long, long time. Many times I could feel my heart racing and my mouth dropping open. It feels good to read a book that sucks you in and keeps you there until you finish. I checked this out at the library on a Thursday afternoon and here it is Saturday night and I&apos;m done. I&apos;ll be passing it off to my mom. Kinda thankful it will be out of my house! Seriously, this story is dark one.</span>
  <span id="freeText18444472775273908853" style="display:none">The Winter People is one of the scariest books I have read in a long, long time. Many times I could feel my heart racing and my mouth dropping open. It feels good to read a book that sucks you in and keeps you there until you finish. I checked this out at the library on a Thursday afternoon and here it is Saturday night and I'm done. I'll be passing it off to my mom. Kinda thankful it will be out of my house! Seriously, this story is dark one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18444472775273908853" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


